The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 February is 204,113 (23,525.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 January, there were 11,271 new confirmed cases (1,299.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 January, there were 10,068 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% (1,203 extra cases).
